warning: {"blocks":[{"key":"5j8hf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"30g95","text":"Safety Precautions:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":19}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1u937","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"985je","text":"All the MIC procedures should be taking place in a designated area at the lab.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"attjc","text":"Before and after processing of the samples, the workstation should be disinfectant with 70% ethanol or 10 % bleach, and all the tools used during the processing must be sterilized.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"85tuv","text":"A properly fastened laboratory coat, long pants/skirt, closed toed shoes and gloves are required when working with clinical isolates.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9deue","text":"After handling any contaminated samples, gloves must be removed, and hands must be washed properly.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ko2s","text":"All contaminated materials and gloves must be discarded in the biohazard containers.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fr0gs","text":"Prior to disposal, decontaminate all waste with 70% ethanol or 10% bleach.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
